Show this link to kids between 10 and 85. A safe, 
fascinating and cheap entry into the physics of model 
rockets using air pressure, water and plastic soda 
bottles. 

http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/pagrosse/h2oRock
etIndex.htm

(Sorry about the formatting, I hate this editor)

I've played with this stuff for about 10 years with many 
hundreds of launches and absolutely no injuries or 
damage. You might have seen a few launches at Buses by 
the Bridge and Jerome.

 -Harry in Fresno
 
